        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-04-21 16:39:15.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-30 ldlm: improve & cleanup ldlm_handle_enqueue0",
        "message": "LU-30 ldlm: improve & cleanup ldlm_handle_enqueue0\n\nThis patch includes a few things:\n- ldlm_namespace::ns_policy is replaced by a new function table\n  ldlm_it_policy_ops, which has two methos:\n  ipo_check: check if intent policy should be executed\n  ipo_handle: intent handler\n\n- intent handler is moved from ldlm_lock_enqueue() to a dedicated\n  function ldlm_lock_intend()\n\n- ldlm_handle_enqueue0 will create ldlm_lock for ns_policy only if\n  it's necessary\n\n- ldlm_handle_enqueue0 will not call ldlm_reprocess_all() anymore\n  even when ELDLM_OK is returned by intent policy\n\n- code cleanup\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang.zhen@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I57a856886456cfb1f929379db20cb74e01d55b64\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_4"
    }
  },
